A Nakuru court has sentenced a boda-boda operator found guilty of child pornography to 15 years in prison. Nakuru senior resident magistrate Eunice Kelly in a ruling said the court having considered the contents of its judgment and mitigation presented in court a custodial sentence was fit for tom Kidemi. Kidemi, a father of five faced six counts relating to sexual offences. The man has been accused of forcing children to engage in sexual acts, promoting child prostitution, child pornography and sex among children. He is said to have committed the offences at his home in railways estate, Nakuru County, on diverse dates in March 2017.